  "body": "The install script [here](\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/zeppelin-solidity/blob/master/scripts/install.sh) writes the contracts subdir directly into my working tree, which is not something I expect any node module to do. I'm also using (and depend on) truffle@beta, so I don't need the files in the worktree at all.\r\n\r\nWhat's worse is that this breaks `truffle compile` for my whole project, because some of the push/pull contracts are missing `payable` modifiers:\r\n\r\n```\r\nError compiling:\r\n\r\n/private/tmp/simplewrite/contracts/zeppelin/examples/BadPushPayments.sol:10:7: Warning: \"msg.value\" used in non-payable function. Do you want to add the \"payable\" modifier to this function?\r\n                if (msg.value < highestBid) throw;\r\n                    ^-------^\r\n,/private/tmp/simplewrite/contracts/zeppelin/examples/BadPushPayments.sol:20:17: Warning: \"msg.value\" used in non-payable function. Do you want to add the \"payable\" modifier to this function?\r\n          highestBid = msg.value;\r\n                       ^-------^\r\n,/private/tmp/simplewrite/contracts/zeppelin/examples/GoodPullPayments.sol:8:9: Warning: \"msg.value\" used in non-payable function. Do you want to add the \"payable\" modifier to this function?\r\n    if (msg.value < highestBid) throw;\r\n        ^-------^\r\n,/private/tmp/simplewrite/contracts/zeppelin/examples/GoodPullPayments.sol:15:18: Warning: \"msg.value\" used in non-payable function. Do you want to add the \"payable\" modifier to this function?\r\n    highestBid = msg.value;\r\n                 ^-------^\r\n,/private/tmp/simplewrite/contracts/zeppelin/examples/PullPaymentBid.sol:10:9: Warning: \"msg.value\" used in non-payable function. Do you want to add the \"payable\" modifier to this function?\r\n    if (msg.value <= highestBid) throw;\r\n        ^-------^\r\n,/private/tmp/simplewrite/contracts/zeppelin/examples/PullPaymentBid.sol:16:18: Warning: \"msg.value\" used in non-payable function. Do you want to add the \"payable\" modifier to this function?\r\n    highestBid = msg.value;\r\n                 ^-------^\r\n,/private/tmp/simplewrite/contracts/zeppelin/examples/StoppableBid.sol:15:9: Warning: \"msg.value\" used in non-payable function. Do you want to add the \"payable\" modifier to this function?\r\n    if (msg.value <= highestBid) throw;\r\n        ^-------^\r\n,/private/tmp/simplewrite/contracts/zeppelin/examples/StoppableBid.sol:21:18: Warning: \"msg.value\" used in non-payable function. Do you want to add the \"payable\" modifier to this function?\r\n    highestBid = msg.value;\r\n                 ^-------^\r\nCompiliation failed. See above.\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnyone installing and attempting to build my project will then fail. Can we remove this as the default behavior?",
