    "body": "@parkan thanks for reporting.\r\nThe compilation error is clearly a problem, and thanks for fixing it here: https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/zeppelin-solidity/pull/118 (merged)\r\n\r\nAs for the copying of files, that's a temporary measure until `npm` integration for truffle is released on a truffle stable version. I also use truffle beta, but we can't expect/require all Zeppelin users to rely on a beta version of the tool. I understand and share the annoying feeling about having [that post-install script](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/zeppelin-solidity/blob/master/scripts/install.sh) that copies Zeppelin files to the worktree, but I don't see any other reasonable option today.\r\n\r\nMaybe @tcoulter has something to say here?\r\n@parkan thanks for raising this issue, developer experience is one of the top priorities for Zeppelin (along with security)\r\n\r\n",
